									Jenkins
									
1-: What is jenkins:
		Jenkins is an open-source automation server that facilitates continuous integration and continuous delivery (CI/CD) of software development projects. It 
		enables automated building, testing, and deployment, helping teams streamline their development processes.

2-: Why use jenkins: 
		Jenkins is used to automate and streamline the software development lifecycle by enabling continuous integration, testing, and deployment, enhancing 
		collaboration and efficiency in development teams.
		
3-: Installation of Jenkins:	
		Step1- Install java in the localserver or live server.
			sudo apt update
			sudo apt install fontconfig openjdk-17-jre
			
		     check install or not java-: java -version
		 
		 Step2- Install jenkins. 
		 	sudo wget -O /usr/share/keyrings/jenkins-keyring.asc \
			  https://pkg.jenkins.io/debian-stable/jenkins.io-2023.key
			  
			echo deb [signed-by=/usr/share/keyrings/jenkins-keyring.asc] \
			  https://pkg.jenkins.io/debian-stable binary/ | sudo tee \
			  /etc/apt/sources.list.d/jenkins.list > /dev/null
			  
			sudo apt-get update
			sudo apt-get install jenkins
			
		Step3- Login.
		      Get password: sudo cat /var/jenkins_home/secrets/initialAdminPassword 
		      Username	:   admin
		      host	: http://localhost:8080

